n- Modify: `crates/ember-core/src/lib.rs:501-506` (passthrough)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `LastMessagePreview` struct to ember-storage**\n\nIn `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs`, add after the `StoredMessage` struct (around line 53):\n\n```rust\n/// Preview data for the most recent message in a conversation.\n/// Used by the TUI conversation list to show message snippets and timestamps.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct LastMessagePreview {\n    pub body: String,\n    pub created_at: i64,\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update `get_last_message_per_contact` return type and SQL**\n\nIn `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs`, change the method signature and implementation:\n\n```rust\npub fn get_last_message_per_contact(\n    &self,\n    contact_ids: &[i64],\n) -> Result<HashMap<i64, LastMessagePreview>, StorageError> {\n    if contact_ids.is_empty() {\n        return Ok(HashMap::new());\n    }\n\n    let conn = self.conn.lock().map_err(|_| StorageError::LockPoisoned)?;\n    let mut result = HashMap::new();\n\n    // Chunk to stay within SQLite's bound-parameter limit\n    for chunk in contact_ids.chunks(Self::SQLITE_MAX_BOUND_VARIABLES) {\n        let placeholders: Vec<&str> = chunk.iter().map(|_| \"?\").collect();\n        let sql = format!(\n            \"SELECT m.contact_id, m.body, m.created_at\n             FROM messages m\n             INNER JOIN (\n                 SELECT contact_id, MAX(id) AS max_id\n                 FROM messages\n                 WHERE contact_id IN ({})\n                   AND content_type = 'text'\n                   AND body IS NOT NULL\n                 GROUP BY contact_id\n             ) latest ON m.id = latest.max_id\",\n            placeholders.join(\", \")\n        );\n\n        let mut stmt = conn.prepare(&sql)?;\n        let params_iter = rusqlite::params_from_iter(chunk.iter());\n        let rows = stmt.query_map(params_iter, |row| {\n            let cid: i64 = row.get(0)?;\n            let body: String = row.get(1)?;\n            let created_at: i64 = row.get(2)?;\n            Ok((cid, LastMessagePreview { body, created_at }))\n        })?;\n\n        for row in rows {\n            let (cid, preview) = row?;\n            result.insert(cid, preview);\n        }\n    }\n\n    Ok(result)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Update the `pub use` line to export `LastMessagePreview`**\n\nIn `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs`, find the existing public exports at the top and ensure `LastMessagePreview` is accessible. It's defined as `pub struct` so it's already exported from the crate.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update ember-core passthrough**\n\nIn `crates/ember-core/src/lib.rs`, change:\n\n```rust\npub fn get_last_message_per_contact(\n    &self,\n    contact_ids: &[i64],\n) -> Result<std::collections::HashMap<i64, ember_storage::LastMessagePreview>, ClientError> {\n    Ok(self.storage.get_last_message_per_contact(contact_ids)?)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Update existing tests**\n\nIn `crates/ember-storage/src/lib.rs`, update `test_get_last_message_per_contact` (around line 2997):\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn test_get_last_message_per_contact() {\n    let storage = Storage::in_memory().unwrap();\n    let alice = Identity::generate();\n    let bob = Identity::generate();\n    let alice_id = storage\n        .add_contact(alice.public_id(), Some(\"Alice\"))\n        .unwrap();\n    let bob_id = storage.add_contact(bob.public_id(), Some(\"Bob\")).unwrap();\n\n    store_n_messages(&storage, alice_id, 3);\n    store_n_messages(&storage, bob_id, 5);\n\n    let last = storage\n        .get_last_message_per_contact(&[alice_id, bob_id])\n        .unwrap();\n    assert_eq!(\n        last.get(&alice_id).map(|p| p.body.as_str()),\n        Some(\"msg-2\")\n    );\n    assert_eq!(last.get(&bob_id).map(|p| p.body.as_str()), Some(\"msg-4\"));\n    // Verify timestamps are populated\n    assert!(last.get(&alice_id).unwrap().created_at > 0);\n    assert!(last.get(&bob_id).unwrap().created_at > 0);\n}\n```\n\nAlso update `test_get_last_message_skip