p task shutdown behavior.\n\n### Unit 5: Error Handling & Panic Safety Review\n**Files**: `crates/reme-storage/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-message/src/wire.rs`, `crates/reme-message/src/tombstone.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs`, `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs`\n**Focus**: 30+ `.expect(\"mutex poisoned\")` in storage vs proper error handling in node, `bincode::encode_to_vec().unwrap()` in send paths, panic on broken mDNS invariant, inconsistent `unwrap` vs `?` patterns.\n\n### Unit 6: Architecture & State Management Review\n**Files**: `crates/reme-core/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-storage/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-outbox/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/coordinator.rs`, `crates/reme-message/src/dag.rs`\n**Focus**: DAG state not persisted (in-memory only, lost on restart), `Mutex<Connection>` serialization bottleneck, TOCTOU in `prepare_message()` (ack_secret stored before outbox enqueue), deprecated `ReceiverConfig` migration stalled, single-connection SQLite under async.\n\n### Unit 7: Secret & Credential Management Review\n**Files**: `crates/reme-identity/src/encrypted.rs`, `apps/node/src/config.rs`, `apps/node/src/node_identity.rs`, `apps/client/src/config.rs`\n**Focus**: `Some(b\"\")` password silently skips encryption, node password plaintext in TOML with no env var support, Windows identity file lacks ACLs, MQTT credentials lacking env var support, `Identity::to_bytes()` returning raw secret.\n\n### Unit 8: Wire Format & Deserialization Review\n**Files**: `crates/reme-message/src/wire.rs`, `crates/reme-message/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-node-core/src/mailbox_store.rs`\n**Focus**: No fuzz testing for wire format parsing (primary attack surface), deserialization failures silently delete mailbox rows, type discriminator validation, body size limits, missing size pre-validation on client send path.\n\n### Unit 9: Concurrency & Resource Management Review\n**Files**: `crates/reme-storage/src/lib.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/mqtt_target.rs`, `crates/reme-discovery/src/mdns_sd.rs`, `apps/node/src/cleanup.rs`\n**Focus**: `stop_advertising` TOCTOU race, MQTT event loop race on target recreation, cleanup task no graceful shutdown, RoundRobin AtomicUsize race (benign), `std::sync::Mutex` in async context.\n\n### Unit 10: Configuration & Operational Hardening Review\n**Files**: `apps/node/src/config.rs`, `apps/client/src/config.rs`, `crates/reme-config/src/lib.rs`\n**Focus**: Missing validation (zero `max_peers`, zero `attempt_timeout_secs`), health endpoint version fingerprinting, no operational metrics/prometheus, no structured delivery failure logging, default-insecure configuration patterns.\n\n## E2E Test Recipe\n\nThis is a review-only task. No code changes. No e2e verification needed. Each agent produces a findings report as a PR comment or document.\n\n## Worker Instructions\n\nEach agent will:\n1. Read the specified files thoroughly\n2. Produce a structured findings report with severity ratings, file:line citations, and recommended fixes\n3. Cross-reference against the existing threat model (`docs/threat-model.md`)\n4. Report as a consolidated finding document — no code changes\n",
