            "content": "# ARCH-M1: Remove deprecated `ReceiverConfig` / `MessageReceiver` / `ReceiverHandle`\n\n## Context\n\nThe `receiver.rs` module was deprecated in v0.4.0 when `TransportCoordinator::subscribe()` superseded `MessageReceiver`. However, the cleanup was never completed:\n\n- `ReceiverConfig` is still embedded as a field in `CoordinatorConfig` (the coordinator's public API)\n- `MessageReceiver` and `ReceiverHandle` are still used in 3 integration tests\n- 9 `#[allow(deprecated)]` suppressions are scattered across the codebase\n- The deprecated types are still re-exported from `reme-transport`'s public API\n\nThis blocks a clean postcard migration because the migration will touch coordinator and wire format paths — doing this cleanup first avoids mixed concerns in that PR.\n\n**No backwards compatibility needed** — project is research/prototype stage with no external users.\n\n## Plan\n\n### Step 1: Inline `poll_interval` into `CoordinatorConfig`\n\n**File: `crates/reme-transport/src/coordinator.rs`**\n\nReplace:\n```rust\n#[allow(deprecated)]\nuse crate::receiver::ReceiverConfig;\n\npub struct CoordinatorConfig {\n    pub routing_strategy: RoutingStrategy,\n    #[allow(deprecated)]\n    pub receiver_config: ReceiverConfig,\n}\n```\n\nWith:\n```rust\npub struct CoordinatorConfig {\n    pub routing_strategy: RoutingStrategy,\n    /// How often to poll HTTP targets for new messages (default: 5s).\n    #[derivative(Default(value = \"Duration::from_secs(5)\"))]\n    pub poll_interval: Duration,\n}\n```\n\nUpdate `spawn_http_receiver` (line 274) to read `self.config.poll_interval` directly instead of `self.config.receiver_config.poll_interval`.\n\nRemove the `#[allow(deprecated)]` on the import (line 24), struct field (line 64), and method (line 266).\n\n### Step 2: Delete `receiver.rs` entirely\n\n**File: `crates/reme-transport/src/receiver.rs`** — delete.\n\nThe entire module (`ReceiverConfig`, `ReceiverHandle`, `MessageReceiver`, `polling_loop`, and two trivial unit tests) is removed. The coordinator's `spawn_http_receiver` already reimplements the same polling loop with deduplication — `receiver.rs` is dead code.\n\n### Step 3: Remove re-exports from `lib.rs`\n\n**File: `crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs`**\n\n- Remove `pub mod receiver;` (line 15)\n- Remove the `#[allow(deprecated)]` + `pub use receiver::{MessageReceiver, ReceiverConfig, ReceiverHandle};` block (lines 44–45)\n\n### Step 4: Update `app.rs` coordinator construction\n\n**File: `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`**\n\nReplace (lines 24, 537–541):\n```rust\n#[allow(deprecated)]\nuse reme_transport::{ReceiverConfig, ...};\n\n#[allow(deprecated)]\nlet coordinator_config = CoordinatorConfig {\n    receiver_config: ReceiverConfig::with_poll_interval(Duration::from_secs(2)),\n    ..CoordinatorConfig::default()\n};\n```\n\nWith:\n```rust\nlet coordinator_config = CoordinatorConfig {\n    poll_interval: Duration::from_secs(2),\n    ..CoordinatorConfig::default()\n};\n```\n\nRemove `ReceiverConfig` from the import and the `#[allow(deprecated)]` annotations.\n\n### Step 5: Remove stale `#[allow(deprecated)]` from `config.rs`\n\n**File: `apps/client/src/config.rs`** (line 598)\n\nRemove `#[allow(deprecated)]` on `RawConfig` — it's stale (no deprecated types are used in that struct).\n\n### Step 6: Migrate integration tests from `MessageReceiver` to `TransportCoordinator`\n\n**File: `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs`**\n\nThree test functions use `MessageReceiver::new(pool).subscribe(routing_key, config)`. Replace each with `TransportCoordinator`:\n\n```rust\n// Before:\nlet receiver = MessageReceiver::new(transport.clone());\nlet config = ReceiverConfig::with_poll_interval(Duration::from_millis(50));\nlet (mut events, _handle) = receiver.subscribe(bob.routing_key(), config);\n\n// After:\nlet mut coordinator = TransportCoordinator::new(CoordinatorConfig {\n    poll_interval: Duration::from_millis(50),\n    ..CoordinatorConfig::default()\n});\ncoordinator.set_http_pool_arc(transport.clone());\nlet (mut events, _handle) = coordinator.subscribe(bob.routing_key());\n```\n\nUpdate imports: remove `MessageReceiver`, `ReceiverConfig`; add `TransportCoordinator`, `CoordinatorConfig`.\n\nRemove the crate-level `#![allow(deprecated)]` (line 6).\n\nWhere the same test reuses the receiver for a second subscription (e.g., Alice's events after Bob's), call `coordinator.subscribe(alice.routing_key())` on the same coordinator instance.\n\n## Files modified\n\n| File | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/coordinator.rs` | Inline `poll_interval`, remove deprecated imports/annotations |\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/receiver.rs` | **Delete** |\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs` | Remove module declaration + re-exports |\n| `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs` | Simplify coordinator config construction |\n| `apps/client/src/config.rs` | Remove stale `#[allow(deprecated)]` |\n| `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs` | Migrate to `TransportCoordinator`, remove deprecated imports |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ncargo fmt --all -- --check\ncargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings\ncargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets\n```\n\nClippy should report zero `deprecated` warnings related to `ReceiverConfig`/`MessageReceiver`/`ReceiverHandle`. A `grep -r \"ReceiverConfig\\|MessageReceiver\\|ReceiverHandle\\|receiver\\.rs\" crates/ apps/` should return no hits.\n",
