            "content": "# Split process_message from tombstone send\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-27\n**Issue:** Message reception delay after action-based event loop refactor\n**Status:** Design\n\n---\n\n## Problem\n\nAfter the action-based TUI event loop refactor (fixing #99/#97), incoming messages appear slower on the recipient's TUI. The root cause: the background drainer calls `client.process_message()` which bundles decrypt + store + tombstone send into one async call. The tombstone send (network I/O, 2-5s on timeout) blocks before the drainer can notify the UI via `Action::MessageProcessed`.\n\nThe industry standard (Matrix, Signal, WhatsApp, RabbitMQ) is **decrypt → display → acknowledge**: show the message to the user immediately after local processing, then send the delivery acknowledgment asynchronously as a fire-and-forget side effect.\n\n## Design\n\n### Split `process_message` into two phases\n\n**Phase 1: `process_message_local`** (sync-safe, no network I/O)\n- Verify routing key\n- Decrypt (MIK)\n- Store pending ack secret\n- Ensure contact exists\n- Store received message (deduplicate)\n- Update DAG tracking\n- Check outbox confirmations\n- Return `ReceivedMessage`\n\n**Phase 2: `send_auto_tombstone`** (async, network I/O)\n- Build `SignedAckTombstone`\n- Submit via transport\n- On success: remove pending ack\n- On failure: log warning (ack_secret persisted for retry)\n\nThe existing `process_message` becomes a thin wrapper calling both in sequence (backward compat for any callers that don't need the split).\n\n### Method signatures\n\n```rust\n/// Process an incoming envelope locally: decrypt, store, update DAG.\n/// Does NOT send tombstone — caller is responsible for that.\npub fn process_message_local(\n    &self,\n    outer: &OuterEnvelope,\n) -> Result<ProcessedMessage, ClientError> { ... }\n\n/// Metadata returned from local processing, needed for tombstone send.\npub struct ProcessedMessage {\n    /// The decrypted message for display\n    pub received: ReceivedMessage,\n    /// Tombstone to send (None if detached message)\n    pub pending_tombstone: Option<SignedAckTombstone>,\n}\n\n/// Send a tombstone for a previously processed message (fire-and-forget).\npub async fn send_tombstone(\n    &self,\n    message_id: MessageID,\n    tombstone: SignedAckTombstone,\n) -> Result<(), ClientError> { ... }\n```\n\n`process_message_local` is NOT async — all operations are local (crypto + SQLite). This is important: it means the drainer can call it, immediately send the action to the UI, then fire-and-forget the tombstone.\n\n### Drainer change\n\n```rust\n// Before:\nlet result = client.process_message(&envelope).await;\ntx.send(Action::MessageProcessed { result, .. });\n\n// After:\nmatch client.process_message_local(&envelope) {\n    Ok(processed) => {\n        // Notify UI immediately — message is decrypted and stored\n        let _ = tx.send(Action::MessageProcessed {\n            result: Ok(processed.received),\n            source,\n        });\n        // Fire-and-forget tombstone (doesn't block next message)\n        if let Some(tombstone) = processed.pending_tombstone {\n            let client = client.clone();\n            let msg_id = envelope.message_id;\n            tokio::spawn(async move {\n                if let Err(e) = client.send_tombstone(msg_id, tombstone).await {\n                    warn!(message_id = ?msg_id, error = %e, \"Tombstone send failed\");\n                }\n            });\n        }\n    }\n    Err(e) => {\n        let _ = tx.send(Action::MessageProcessed {\n            result: Err(e.to_string()),\n            source,\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Backward compatibility\n\nThe existing `process_message` is preserved as a convenience wrapper:\n\n```rust\npub async fn process_message(&self, outer: &OuterEnvelope) -> Result<ReceivedMessage, ClientError> {\n    let processed = self.process_message_local(outer)?;\n    if let Some(tombstone) = processed.pending_tombstone {\n        self.send_tombstone(outer.message_id, tombstone).await?;\n    }\n    Ok(processed.received)\n}\n```\n\nNo other callers need to change.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n- Add `ProcessedMessage` struct to `reme-core`\n- Extract `process_message_local` (sync) from `process_message`\n- Extract `send_tombstone` (async) from `process_message`\n- Keep `process_message` as a wrapper\n- Update both drainers in `spawn_background_tasks` to use the split\n\n### Out of scope\n- Changing the tombstone retry mechanism\n- Modifying the outbox tick path\n- Any TUI changes (the Action enum and update() are unchanged)\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n- `cargo test -p reme-core` — existing tests still pass\n- Manual: send a message, verify it appears on recipient immediately (no tombstone delay)\n- Tombstone still sent (check relay node logs or pending_ack table clears)\n",
